        "## Overview\n",
        "\n",
        "This project compares two approaches to financial news sentiment classification: fine-tuning a pre-trained BERT model versus using a local Gemma 4 model with zero-shot and few-shot prompting.\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-tip}\n",
        "## Full Notebook\n",
        "Download the complete Jupyter notebook with all code and outputs: [View Notebook](../../notebooks/sentiment-analysis.ipynb){target=\"_blank\"}\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "## Dataset Distribution"
      ],
      "id": "afe3eeb6"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "labels = ['Neutral', 'Positive', 'Negative']\n",
        "counts = [3931, 3626, 2443]\n",
        "colors = ['#5bcefa', '#7c73ff', '#e74c3c']\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
        "ax.bar(labels, counts, color=colors)\n",
        "ax.set_title('Sentiment Distribution (10,000 Sample)')\n",
        "ax.set_ylabel('Count')\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
